marc21:datafield.marc21:subfield: Diary containing brief daily entries. Kitson complains about his health, mentions sculptures in progress, and refers to many artists, his patrons and models. He refers to the activities of his wife Theo, also a sculptor, and writes about family matters, taking photographs, and of his trip to New York City, Montreal, and Vicksburg.
Henry Hudson and Theo Alice Ruggles Kitson papers
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
